      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is highly recommended that you do not take a super high dose like 50,000 IU daily without professional guidance. While Vitamin D deficiency is common in Oslo during winter, mega-dosing can lead to toxicity, which is dangerous. Please consult with your doctor or a registered dietitian to determine the appropriate dosage for you. They can test your levels and recommend a safe and effective supplement plan.",
      "source": "target",
